ctrinal foundations of spiritual wayfaring as well as processes and stages that an aspiring wayfarer must go through in order to attain spiritual realization. He discusses the relation between the exoteric and esoteric aspects of Islam and clearly demonstrates that these inward and outward dimensions of Islam complement each other. The book also provides information on the Quranic origins of Sufism and its special relations with Shi'ism as well as the role of Shi'i Imams in the spiritual realization of a sincere wayfarer.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aGod (Islam)xQurʼanic teaching. 0aGod (Islam)xQurʾanic teaching. 0aIslamxEssence, genius, nature. 0aReligious lifexIslamxQurʼanic teaching. 0aReligious lifexIslamxQurʾanic teaching. 0aReligious lifexIslam. 0aReligious lifexShīʻah. 0aReligious lifexShīʿah. 0aSufism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Islam. 7aRELIGION / Islam / Sufi.2bisacsh1 aFaghfoory, Mohammad H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNasr, Seyyed Hossein, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTihrānī, Sayyid Muḥammad Ḥusayn Ḥusaynī, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791489277423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791489277/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles